<html><head></head><body dir=3D"auto" style=3D"overflow-wrap: =
break-word; -webkit-nbsp-mode: space; line-break: =
after-white-space;"><p>Hi Grant,</p><p>I am following up on our visit to =
the property on Tuesday. I left the meeting feeling quite confused about =
several points, and I would be grateful if you could please clarify the =
following so I can properly understand the approach Tower is =
taking:</p><p><b>1. Independent expert testing</b></p><p>You indicated =
that Tower/you will not pay for any expert testing as part of my =
preparation of the claim, as you said that is what you are already =
doing. However, I am struggling to understand this position. =46rom my =
perspective, you are preparing the claim from Tower=E2=80=99s side, and =
I have not been invited to or involved in any of the NZRSC assessments =
or discussions. This does not feel independent or transparent from my =
side.</p><p>Given the seriousness of the fire, and the chemical =
involvement (including spa chemicals with corrosive chlorides and =
bromides), I am concerned that critical risks may be under-assessed. =
Could you please clarify why Tower would not support me in engaging =
independent engineers, hygienists, or other specialists to provide an =
impartial view?</p><p><b>2. Structural elements =E2=80=93 linings and =
framing</b></p><p>You mentioned replacing only a couple of beams and =
using methods such as dry ice blasting and thermal fogging for the =
bricks. Could you please clarify how this is considered adequate given =
that:</p><p><ul class=3D"MailOutline"><li>Smoke odour and residue remain =
even on the first floor =E2=80=94 the least affected part of the house =
=E2=80=94 more than three months after the fire, which suggests deep =
penetration.</li><li>The fire was electrical in origin but also involved =
spa chemicals, meaning corrosive residues (chlorides, bromides) are =
highly likely to have penetrated linings, framing, and =
fixings,</li><li>Painting over materials or superficial cleaning does =
not appear to restore the property to an =E2=80=9Cas new=E2=80=9D =
standard.</li><li>The suggested treatments do not seem to reasonably =
reinstate &nbsp;to an =E2=80=9Cas new=E2=80=9D standard, particularly =
given the dieppe smoke and chemical =
penetration</li></ul><div><br></div></p><div>You mentioned replacing =
only a couple of beams and using methods such as dry-ice blasting and =
thermal fogging for the bricks. =46rom a technical perspective, this =
seems inadequate because:</div><div><br></div><div><ul =
class=3D"MailOutline"><li>Smoke odour and residue remain even on the =
first floor =E2=80=94 the least affected part of the house =E2=80=94 =
three months after the fire, suggesting deep penetration.</li><li>The =
fire involved spa chemicals, creating corrosive residues (chlorides, =
bromides) likely absorbed into linings, timber framing, and =
fixings.</li><li>Superficial cleaning, fogging, or painting over =
residues cannot ensure long-term safety or durability.</li><li>Bricks =
and mortar are porous: once penetrated by smoke and chemical residues, =
they can continue to off-gas and deteriorate over time, undermining both =
habitability and structural performance.</li><li><li>Similarly, timber =
framing, structural timbers, and plasterboard linings are fibrous and =
absorbent. Once smoke and chemical residues penetrate, they may release =
odours, compromise air quality, accelerate corrosion of embedded =
fixings, and create conditions for hidden mould or decay. These risks =
cannot be fully eliminated by surface =
cleaning</li></li></ul></div><p><div>On that basis, could you clarify =
how retaining contaminated bricks, timbers, and linings meets Tower=E2=80=99=
s obligation to reinstate the property to a =E2=80=9Cas new=E2=80=9D =
standard? What testing and certification is planned to ensure these =
critical services are restored to a safe and =E2=80=9Cas new=E2=80=9D =
condition?</div><div><br></div><div><b>3. Roof =
assessment</b></div></p><p>You indicated that the roof requires no work. =
I find this difficult to reconcile with the evidence:</p><p><ul =
class=3D"MailOutline"><li>Large volumes of black smoke were seen coming =
out from all sides of the roof during the fire.</li><li>A gutter was =
significantly heat-damaged.</li><li>Local reporting even suggested the =
fire appeared to be in the roof.</li></ul></p><p>If external heat was =
sufficient to damage guttering, then internal elements such as roof =
cavity insulation, underlay, battens, fixings, and trusses may also have =
been affected. Could you please clarify what inspection methods were =
used to conclude the roof was undamaged? Were cavity inspections, =
intrusive checks, or residue/chemical tests undertaken?</p><p><b>4. =
Services =E2=80=93 gas, electricity, and water</b></p><p>I understand =
that you are going to test the gas unit and propose a plan to bring it =
up to new standard, which I appreciate. However, could you also please =
clarify what is planned for the &nbsp;electricty system, which suffered =
significant and widespread damage and the water distribution =
system</p><p>At present I am unclear how these critical services will be =
properly tested and reinstated. What testing and certification is =
planned to ensure these critical services are restored to a safe and =
=E2=80=9Cas new=E2=80=9D condition?</p><p><b>5. Timing and completeness =
of assessments</b></p><p>I am also confused and &nbsp;concerned that a =
repair plan is already being discussed before full assessments have been =
completed and before I have seen the NZRSC or other formal =
reports.</p><p>Could you clarify why Tower is progressing toward a =
repair plan at this stage rather than awaiting intrusive testing, =
particularly given the involvement of corrosive chemicals and deep smoke =
penetration?</p><p>In addition, is it not too risky to wait until after =
restructuring works to determine whether the house is safe and meets =
code requirements? That approach could prolong reinstatement =
unnecessarily, leaving me at greater disadvantage with accommodation =
costs and delays that are outside my control.</p><p><b>6. Testing and =
reporting</b></p><p>Could you please confirm:</p><p><ul =
class=3D"MailOutline"><li>What tests or assessments have actually been =
completed so far?</li><li>Why, given the involvement of spa chemicals, =
no intrusive testing has been arranged?</li><li>When the NZRSC report =
and other reports will be made available to me?</li><li>What testing and =
certification is planned to ensure my house restored to a safe and =E2=80=9C=
as new=E2=80=9D condition?</li></ul></p><p data-start=3D"286" =
data-end=3D"658"><b>7. Accommodation suppoort</b></p><p>At present, my =
rental accommodation is being covered under the contents policy ($30,000 =
limit). However, the house remains uninhabitable, and delays in =
assessment and reinstatement are entirely beyond my control.</p><p>The =
Fair Insurance Code requires insurers to act fairly and not disadvantage =
customers through delay. The principle of insurance is to restore the =
insured to the pre-loss position. To avoid being unfairly disadvantaged, =
I would like to explore the following options:</p><p><ul =
class=3D"MailOutline"><li>Option A: Tower agrees I may take the lead in =
arranging necessary assessments and reinstatement works, provided all =
works are to =E2=80=9Cas new=E2=80=9D standard, meet current Building =
Code requirements, and remain within the insured sum. Tower would =
reimburse incurred costs within 15 days of invoice on a monthly basis, =
ensuring timely progress without administrative delay.</li><li>Option B: =
Alternatively, Tower confirms that it will continue to cover my =
accommodation costs until the house is fully restored and habitable, =
given that ongoing delays are not of my making.</li></ul></p><p>Could =
you please confirm which of these approaches Tower is prepared to adopt, =
so that I am not unfairly disadvantaged by circumstances outside my =
control?</p><p><b>8. Privacy Act material</b></p><p>You previously =
referred me to information provided under the Privacy Act, but the links =
I received do not open or function. Could you please resend this =
information, ensuring that the links are accessible, or alternatively =
provide the documents as direct PDF/email attachments?</p><p>I would =
greatly appreciate your clarification on each of these points so that I =
can properly understand how my home will be restored to a safe, =E2=80=9Ca=
s new=E2=80=9D standard.</p><p>Kind regards,</p><p>Raffaella del =
Prete</p><div><br></div><div class=3D"AppleOriginalContents" =
style=3D"direction: ltr;"><blockquote type=3D"cite"><div>On 1 Sep 2025, =
